Company Description: Publix Super Market Has Grown Into A Fortune 500 Company With More Than 870 Stores. The Grocery Store Chain Is One Of The Fastest-Growing, Employee-Owned Companies IN The United States. Also Known As One Of The 10 Largest-Volume Supermarket Chains IN The Nation, The Company S Retail Sales Reached Nearly $20 Billion IN 2004. Publix Offers Pharmacy And Photo Development Services Along With Food And Other Grocery Store Items. A Privately Held Company Operating Stores IN Florida, Georgia, South Carolina, Alabama And Tennessee, George W. Jenkins Founded Publix IN Winter Haven, Fla., IN 1930. Publix Super Market Maintains A Location IN Miami.

Founded IN 1930, Publix Super Markets Is One Of The Largest Supermarket Chains IN The United States. The Company Specializes IN A Variety Of Grocery Products, Such As Meat, Seafood, Dairy Items, And Natural And Organic Foods. It Operates Deli, Bakery And Produce Departments. Its Pharmacy Division Offers Medical Screenings And Insurance Services. The Retailer Also Provides Cakes And Desserts For Weddings And Special Occasions. IN Addition, Publix Super Markets Organizes Cooking Classes. It Operates A Food And Nutrition Center That Offers Information On Health, Recipes And Weight Management. The Retailer S Additional Services Include Gift Cards And Film Development. It Publishes A Magazine That Features Articles On Food And Nutrition. With A Presence IN Miami, Publix Super Markets Also Operates Distribution Centers And Manufacturing Facilities.

With Annual Sales Of More Than $23.9 Billion, It Has A Staff Of Over 140,000 Employees. The Chain Maintains Nearly 1,000 Supermarkets IN South Carolina, Alabama And Tennessee. It Operates Publix Pharmacy, Which Provides Prescriptions At More Than 700 Pharmacies Throughout Alabama, Florida And Georgia.
